---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'April 12, 2026';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — DoItSwift"
  description="How DoItSwift handles information when you use our browser-based image tools and website."
  keywords="doitswift privacy policy, browser image privacy"
>
  <section class="legal-doc">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy describes how DoItSwift (“we,” “us,” or “our”) handles information when you visit our
        website and use our tools. We built DoItSwift around <strong>local, in-browser processing</strong> so that
        your images often do not need to be uploaded to our servers to be converted or compressed. Please read this
        policy together with our <a href="/terms" class="link-back">Terms of Service</a> and{' '}
        <a href="/cookies" class="link-back">Cookie Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        DoItSwift operates the website at <a href="https://doitswift.com" class="link-back">doitswift.com</a> (the
        “Site”). For how to reach us, including matters that require a postal or legal address, use the{' '}
        <a href="/contact" class="link-back">contact page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We aim to collect only what we need to run the Site and understand aggregate usage:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical data.</strong> Like most websites, our hosting or infrastructure may automatically log
          information such as IP address, browser type, referring page, and timestamps. The exact logs depend on our
          hosting provider and configuration.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Local storage.</strong> We may store preferences (for example, light or dark theme) in your browser
          using <code>localStorage</code>. This stays on your device.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Files you process.</strong> When a tool runs entirely in your browser, your images are processed on
          your device. We do not receive those files in that mode. If we later add server-side features (accounts,
          cloud conversion, support uploads), we will update this policy to describe what is collected and why.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <p>We use information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Operate, secure, and improve the Site and tools</li>
        <li>Understand aggregated usage patterns (for example, which pages are popular)</li>
        <li>Respond to lawful requests and protect our rights, if applicable</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We may use cookies or similar technologies where necessary for Site functionality or analytics. See our{' '}
        <a href="/cookies" class="link-back">Cookie Policy</a> for more detail. You can control cookies through your
        browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        Our pages may load resources from third parties (for example, font providers, script CDNs, or affiliate
        partners). Those providers have their own privacy practices. We encourage you to review their policies. Links to
        partner sites may include identifiers used for attribution; follow their terms when you leave our Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or restrict certain data, or to
        object to processing. To exercise rights that apply to information we hold as a controller, contact us via the{' '}
        <a href="/contact" class="link-back">contact page</a>. We may need to verify your request.
      </p>

      <h2>International users</h2>
      <p>
        If you access the Site from outside the country where servers are located, your information may be processed in
        countries with different data protection laws. We take steps designed to protect information in line with this
        policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information only as long as needed for the purposes described here and as required by law. Server logs
        and analytics retention periods depend on our hosting and analytics configuration.
      </p>

      <h2>Security</h2>
      <p>
        No method of transmission over the Internet is completely secure. We use reasonable measures appropriate to the
        nature of the Site. Because many tools run locally in your browser, you also control the files on your device.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the new date at the top and, where appropriate,
        provide additional notice. Continued use of the Site after changes means you accept the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Reach us through the <a href="/contact" class="link-back">contact page</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="disclaimer">
        <strong>General information.</strong> This policy is provided as a helpful template for a browser-first tool
        site. It is not legal advice. Have it reviewed by a qualified attorney for your jurisdiction, business
        structure, and any advertising, analytics, or accounts you enable.
      </p>

      <p><a href="/" class="link-back">← Back to home</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
